📘 Process Exporter Installation Guide
This guide explains how to install and configure Process Exporter on a Linux server with systemd support.


✅ Prerequisites

Linux machine (Ubuntu / CentOS / RHEL)

wget, tar, and systemd installed
Root or sudo access
Basic CLI knowledge



🧱 Step 1: Create Application Directory

sudo mkdir -p /apps




📥 Step 2: Download Process Exporter

wget https://github.com/ncabatoff/process-exporter/releases/download/v0.7.5/process-exporter-0.7.5.linux-amd64.tar.gz




📦 Step 3: Extract Archive

tar -xvf process-exporter-0.7.5.linux-amd64.tar.gz




🔄 Step 4: Rename and Move Folder

mv process-exporter-0.7.5.linux-amd64 process-exporter




🧹 Step 5: Cleanup Archive File

rm -rf process-exporter-0.7.5.linux-amd64.tar.gz




⚙️ Step 6: Create Configuration File

sudo vi /apps/process-exporter/config.yaml


Paste the following YAML:

process_names:
  - name: "{{.Comm}}"
    cmdline:
    - '.+'
  - comm:
    - Prometheus




🔧 Step 7: Create systemd Service File

sudo vi /etc/systemd/system/process-exporter.service


Paste the following:

[Unit]
Description=Process Exporter
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=root
Group=root
WorkingDirectory=/apps/process-exporter
ExecStart=/apps/process-exporter/process-exporter -config.path config.yaml
KillMode=process
SuccessExitStatus=143
TimeoutSec=10
RestartSec=1
SyslogIdentifier=process-exporter
LimitNOFILE=1000000
LimitCORE=infinity

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target




🚀 Step 8: Start and Enable Service
Reload systemd and start the service:

sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl start process-exporter.service
sudo systemctl enable process-exporter.service


Check service status:

sudo systemctl status process-exporter.service




⚠️ Troubleshooting Tips
Check logs for errors:

sudo journalctl -u process-exporter.service -f


If service doesn’t start:

Verify config.yaml syntax
Ensure binary path /apps/process-exporter/process-exporter is correct
Confirm no conflicting ports
